{"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10101-Discover-rolling-clips-with-ReplayKit","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","type":"reference"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"text":"Related Sessions","anchor":"Related-Sessions","type":"heading"},{"style":"list","items":["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10081-Tap-into-virtual-and-physical-game-controllers","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10633-Capture-and-stream-apps-on-the-Mac-with-ReplayKit"],"type":"links"}],"kind":"content"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Never again miss anyone’s great moment in your game or app. Learn about ReplayKit’s latest update — clips screen recording — which provides your app with a rolling buffer of past video and audio samples. When memorable moments happen, discover how you can record and save it for people, and find out how you can surface those clips when they’re most relevant. Lastly, we’ll take you through integrating ReplayKit into your iOS and macOS apps.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"title":"Discover rolling clips with ReplayKit","roleHeading":"WWDC21","role":"sampleCode","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}]},"kind":"article","sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2021\/10101","overridingTitle":"Watch Video (8 min)"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10101-discover-rolling-clips-with-replaykit"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21"]]},"references":{"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentation/wwdcnotes/contributing":{"identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","url":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing","title":"Learn More…","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn More…"}],"type":"link"},"WWDC21.jpeg":{"alt":null,"type":"image","variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21.jpeg","traits":["1x","light"]}],"identifier":"WWDC21.jpeg"},"https://developer.apple.com/videos/play/wwdc2021/10101":{"checksum":null,"type":"download","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2021\/10101","url":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/videos\/play\/wwdc2021\/10101"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC20-10633-Capture-and-stream-apps-on-the-Mac-with-ReplayKit":{"role":"sampleCode","kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC20-10633-Capture-and-stream-apps-on-the-Mac-with-ReplayKit","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc20-10633-capture-and-stream-apps-on-the-mac-with-replaykit","title":"Capture and stream apps on the Mac with ReplayKit","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Learn how you can integrate ReplayKit into your Mac apps and games to easily share screen recordings or broadcast live audio and visuals online. We’ll show you how to capture screen content, audio, and microphone input inside your Mac apps, and even broadcast your video to a live audience."}]},"WWDC21-Icon.png":{"identifier":"WWDC21-Icon.png","alt":null,"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-Icon.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes","images":[{"type":"icon","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png"}],"abstract":[{"text":"Session notes shared by the community for the community.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"collection","title":"WWDC Notes"},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21","type":"topic","kind":"article","images":[{"identifier":"WWDC21-Icon.png","type":"icon"},{"identifier":"WWDC21.jpeg","type":"card"}],"url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21","title":"WWDC21","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Xcode 13, Swift 5.5, iOS 15, macOS 12 (Monterey), tvOS 15, watchOS 8."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"New APIs: "},{"code":"MusicKit","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"DocC","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"code":"StoreKit 2","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", and more."}],"role":"collectionGroup"},"WWDCNotes.png":{"variants":[{"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDCNotes.png","traits":["1x","light"]}],"type":"image","identifier":"WWDCNotes.png","alt":null},"doc://WWDCNotes/documentation/WWDCNotes/WWDC21-10081-Tap-into-virtual-and-physical-game-controllers":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC21-10081-Tap-into-virtual-and-physical-game-controllers","url":"\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc21-10081-tap-into-virtual-and-physical-game-controllers","abstract":[{"text":"It’s time to up your input game: Learn about the latest improvements to virtual and physical game controllers for iPhone, iPad, Mac, and Apple TV. Meet the virtual on-screen controller, which turns touch input into game controller input, and find out how to add controller sharing features to your app. We’ll also show you how to support adaptive trigger technology found in DualSense controllers, provide best practices for controller support, and take you through some common pre-flight checks around accessible and customizable input before submitting to the App Store.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","kind":"article","role":"sampleCode","title":"Tap into virtual and physical game controllers"}}}